The paper discusses a novel output layer modification for neural networks to learn latent annotations in a partially supervised setting. This involves both supervised classification and unsupervised clustering, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also applies this approach to image classification, which falls under computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
